#stance=stance1
#originalStanceText=After Conception
#originalTopic=when-does-life-begin
Rome was not built in a day. While we can easily glorify the act of creating something new, it is much harder to pinpoint the instant it happened. In fact, with complex creations, there is no instant to glorify - only a process of incremental accrual of characteristics.Also, there is nothing inevitable about a fetal clump of cells becoming a human being. Many, perhaps most, conceptions fail naturally. Biology is harsh.